## When asked to commit
- If on the default branch (`main`/`master`): create a new branch first.
- Commit messages follow the repo convention: `{{COMMIT_CONVENTION}}` (e.g. `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`).
- One logical change per commit; don't bundle unrelated work.

## Branch & PR
- Branch naming convention: {{BRANCH_NAMING}}.
- PR rules: {{PR_RULES}}.

## Monorepo
- git lives at the root only; never git init inside `be/`, `fe/`.
